x4freetext: The alpha-particles were detected with semiconductor
detectors prepared at the KINR with an energy
resolution of about 50 keV and a sensitive region
thickness of 400-1000 mu-m.
Measurements were made simultaneously in eight
detectors located at different angles relative to the
beam. Four detectors were in the forward hemisphere
at a distance of 15-30 cm from the target, and the
remaining detectors were located at large angles at a
distance of 11-14 cm from the target.
Self-supporting film with 1.00 mg/cm2 thick.
Impurity Mo - 20-25%.
